# HTML / Templates

## Semantic structure

Always use HTML5 semantic tags:
- `<header role="banner">`, `<footer role="contentinfo">`, `<nav role="navigation">`, `<main id="content" role="main">`
- Strict heading hierarchy `h1 > h2 > h3`, **only one `h1` per page**
- `<section>` for thematic sections, `<article>` for standalone content

## Project-specific conventions

- Main wrappers: `.header-wrap`, `.footer-wrap`
- Bootstrap container: prefer `.container.container-xl` (this is the starter's standard combo)
- Skip link: `<a class="accessibility-content-link visually-hidden-focusable" href="#content">Skip to content</a>` as the very first child of `<body>`
- Logo: `<a class="header-logo">` with `<span class="visually-hidden">Home</span>`
- `<html class="no-js">` on load → swapped to `js` by an inline script in `<head>` (lets CSS gracefully handle no-JS states):

```html
<html class="no-js">
  <head>
    <!-- Placed early, before external scripts -->
    <script>(function(html){html.className = html.className.replace(/\bno-js\b/,'js')})(document.documentElement);</script>
  </head>
```

## Google Fonts — non-blocking pattern

Always load Google Fonts asynchronously (preconnect + preload with `onload` swap + `<noscript>` fallback) to avoid render-blocking requests:

```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link rel="preload"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=<Font>:wght@400;600;700&display=swap"
      as="style"
      onload="this.onload=null;this.rel='stylesheet'">
<noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=<Font>:wght@400;600;700&display=swap"></noscript>
```

## Required accessibility

- Any meaningful image → descriptive `alt`; decorative → `alt=""`
- Any icon-only button → `<span class="visually-hidden">Label</span>` inside
- `aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, `aria-expanded`, `aria-hidden` depending on context
- Do **not** put `aria-labelledby` on `<section>` by default. Prefer a visible heading (`<h2>`, `<h3>`) inside the section.
- Decorative `<i class="icon-…">` glyphs → `aria-hidden="true"`
- Bootstrap dropdowns: `data-bs-toggle="dropdown"` + `aria-expanded="false"`
- Splide / Swiper carousels: `aria-roledescription="carousel"` on the root, `aria-live="polite"` on the track

## Buttons vs links (global rule)

- **Action** (toggle, open modal, submit, tabs, carousel arrows, filters) ⇒ use `<button>` with explicit `type` (`button|submit|reset`).
- **Navigation** (go to another URL / route / anchor) ⇒ use `<a href="…">`.
- Never use `<a href="#">` as a fake button.

## Reusable blocks

- `www/templates/blocks/` = reusable components (carousel, cookie, push…)
- `www/templates/pages/` = full pages that compose blocks
- Factor out: if a pattern appears ≥ 2 times, create a block

## Examples

```php
// ❌ BAD
<div class="title">Our services</div>
<div class="button" onclick="...">See more</div>

// ✅ GOOD
<h2 class="default-title">Our services</h2>
<a href="/services" class="btn btn-primary btn-arrow-right-link">
  See more <span class="visually-hidden">of our services</span>
</a>
```
